Things to do for each release


Version 0.1
   - OpenCL backend
   - Basic platform detection
   - Low-level generic API to manage platform
      - Allocation/Release
      - Direct data transfers

Version 0.2
   - Generic kernel management
   - Basic kernel execution (static scheduling)
      - Generic kernel parameters

Version 0.3
   - Indirect data transfers (through main memory for instance)

Version 1.0
   - Kernel scheduling


Version N
   - Functional frontend
      - Parallel interpreter
      - Garbage collector
   - Granularity adaptation
   - Fault-tolerance
      - Automatic check-pointing
   - Schedulers
   - Kernel generation
      - Data-parallel
   - Backends
      - CUDA
      - x86
      - Simulator
      - Hard-drive
   - Kernel library
      - Automatic tests
      - Auto-tuning (perf model)
   - Networking
      - Global-view
      - Hierarchical
      - MPI-like
   - Performance models
   - Accuracy management
